net.proteusframework.cms.component.generator

Interface Generator<T extends PageElement>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of bean the Generator is generating content.
    All Superinterfaces:
    Cacheable<T>, Renderer<T>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    ScriptGenerator<G>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractScriptGenerator, CmsIntegration, DelegateGenerator, GeneratorImpl, HTMLBoxGenerator, HTMLPageGenerator, MIWTGenerator, PageSyndicationGenerator, PassthroughGenerator, SequentialGenerator, XMLGenerator

    public interface Generator<T extends PageElement>
extends Renderer<T>, Cacheable<T>
    Renderer for content that provides caching information.
    Generator instances will only be used by one thread at a time.
    The lifetime of the Generator is the request/response cycle.

    It is guaranteed that the following methods will called in the order listed only once per request.

    • getDataSourceTimestamp
    • getIdentity
    • getScope
    • getExpireTime
    • preRenderProcess
    • getNDEs
    • render

    NOTE: the method getIdentity is meant to replace getDataSourceTimestamp. When writing new Generators, it is best to implement getIdentity since getDataSourceTimestamp will eventually be removed.

    A generator is responsible for gathering caching information (scope, identity, dataSourceTimestamp, expireTime) on the content that it generates. This requirement does not include any content generated due to delegation to other PageElements that provide their own Generators; however, it does apply to the use of DelegateRenderers.

    For more information on delegation, see:

    • PageElement.getChildPageElements(CmsRequest)
    • ProcessChain.delegatePreRenderProcessing(DelegateRenderer)
    • ProcessChain.delegatePreRenderProcessing(PageElement)
    • ProcessChain.delegatePreRenderProcessing(DelegateRenderer, PageElement)
    • RenderChain.delegateRender(DelegateRenderer)
    • RenderChain.delegateRender(PageElement)
    • RenderChain.delegateRender(DelegateRenderer, PageElement)

    Author:
    Russ Tennant (russ@i2rd.com)

    • Method Detail

      • getDataSourceTimestamp

        long getDataSourceTimestamp(CmsRequest<T> request)
        Get the latest timestamp of the data being used to generate the content. The timestamp should be for the content being generated by the generator. The timestamp should not represent data from other elements in the process chain with the exception of delegates not processed by CMS. This method is guaranteed to be called for every CMS (http / servlet) request.
        Parameters:
        request - the request.
        Returns:
        the timestamp or -1 if unknown.

      • getExpireTime

        long getExpireTime()
        Get the expire time of the generated content. This method must never return a negative value. Content generators must always specify a valid expire time.
        Specified by:
        getExpireTime in interface Cacheable<T extends PageElement>
        Returns:
        the expire time in millis or 0 if it expires immediately. Return -1 to indicate that the expire time from this Cacheable shouldn't be used unless otherwise specified.
